The article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on Flag Day, which is celebrated on June 14th. The proclamation highlights the significance of the American flag as a symbol of unity, liberty, and justice. It mentions notable moments in history where the flag was raised, such as the Battle of Iwo Jima and the moon landing. The proclamation also calls on Americans to honor the flag and pay respect to those who have sacrificed their lives for the country. It states that June 14th is recognized as Flag Day and the week in which it falls as National Flag Week. The President urges all citizens to display the flag during this time and to observe with pride the days from Flag Day through Independence Day.